Fox News Host Sean Hannity told former White House Chief Strategist Steve Bannon that the two of them, along with others who have derided special counsel Robert Mueller's investigation, "may end up in jail" for their staunch support of President Donald Trump.

On Monday night, Hannity sat down with Bannon, who has returned to a leadership position at the hard-right media site Breitbart, and Fox News Political Analyst Pat Goodell, on a special edition of "Breitbart News Tonight."
